{
  "stem": "2916.5",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You see, all along we were under the impression that the American Air Force attacked us because they saw that it was a military train.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And also, the head of the train, the commandant, was captured in Seeshaupt and later interrogated by the Americans, he told that he had order.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Why was he heading for Austria, they asked him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So he said, because he was given an order to take the train into a tunnel in the Austrian Alps and blow it up.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But now I found out during this commemoration-- you see, the people of Seeshaupt were planning this for a long time.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were doing research into the whole event because they really didn't know much about it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So based on declassified documents, they found out something very, very spectacular, very amazing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I'm going to shorten this.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You see, Hitler was building a Alpine Fortress, it was called.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And people who study the history of World War II-- they know about it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Whoever I mention to and is knowledgeable knew that a fortress was being built in a very deep valley called Otztal in Austria, in the Austrian Alps, in the very high Alps.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And there, Hitler was going to build a cement haven, like an enormous bunker, for his surviving army.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And so when the Americans and the British were closing in on his armies, he was going to ship them to Otztal with all the remaining ammunition and continue the war from there.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the Allies knew about it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And they knew that that fortress was impenetrable.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They wouldn't be able to destroy it, and the war would have continued for a long time after it actually ended.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So it would have caused many more American casualties.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
